HEADWORD: Convener
<hw>Con*ven"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
convenes or meets with others.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who calls an assembly together or convenes a
meeting; hence, the chairman of a committee or other organized
body.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conveniency</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Convenience</ent>⟦br⟧
